  "markdown_content": "\n## Executive Summary\n\nUser requested automated Gmail scanning for January 2026 receipts with expense categorization into spreadsheet format. Manus identified authentication limitations (no stored credentials) and requested clarification on access method (browser automation vs Gmail API) and categorization logic. Session ended with user responding 'continue' but no specific approach selected.\n\n\n## Context & Intent\n\nExpense management automation task requiring Gmail access and intelligent receipt categorization\n\n\n## What Was Done\n\nProblem scoping and constraint identification - highlighted authentication barriers and presented alternative approaches\n\n\n## Outputs Produced\n\n- [analysis] technical requirements assessment — identified Gmail access limitations and alternative approaches\n- [clarification request] implementation options — browser automation vs API vs alternative methods\n\n## Lessons Learned\n\nWorked well:\n\n- proactive identification of authentication constraints\n- clear presentation of alternative approaches\nFailed / suboptimal:\n\n- session incomplete - user provided unclear continuation signal\nDiscoveries:\n\n- environment credentials unavailable\n- Google blocks direct password authentication\n\n## Challenges & Blockers\n\n- missing Gmail credentials\n- ambiguous user response to continuation options\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- which access method to use\n- categorization logic preferences\n- merchant/keyword mapping rules\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- await user selection of access method\n- define categorization rules\n- implement chosen approach\n---\nUID: Q7TUpL9KFuEgH6RhHpw3h3 | Model: claude-sonnet-4-20250514 | Cost: $0.0101\n"
}